                  <msItem class="#liturgica #musica" n="1" xml:id="MS_Barlow_7-item1">
                     <title key="work_13914" type="desc">Pontifical of the <orgName key="org_124759589"><!-- links to Evesham abbey -->Abbot of Evesham</orgName>, with music</title>
                  <note><p>The chief contents are:</p></note>
                  <note>The services for baptism (p. 32); ordination and profession (p. 45); marriage (p. 63);
                     benedictions (p. 81); processions (p. 101); and the offices of the sick and dead (p. 185)</note>
                  <note>15th-century forms of prayers (p. iv); for the installation of a new abbot (p. v); 
                  for confraternity (p. vii); absolution from excommunication (p. ix); for Henry IV and his queen Joanna 
                  and for Margaret, wife of Henry VI (altered to Elizabeth, for Edward IV), and her son Edward, 
                  prince of Wales (p. xi)</note>
                  <note>(Edited by H. A. Wilson for the Henry Bradshaw Society (vol. vi, 1893), with the additional matter on pp. iv-xiv there printed in appendix)</note>
                  <note><p>Also a table of contents by <persName key="person_465">Thomas Barlow</persName> (p. xiii)</p></note>
                  
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  
